  | If you want to learn some basic (initial) setup for the Pi, including tips on selecting the right kind of SD cardm wifi adapter etc. then check out
  a[href="http://markclittle.blogspot.co.uk/2012/12/adventures-in-pi-land-part-one.html"]
    |  this article
  |.
p
  | Various people have written up the work that they're doing in porting our projects to devices such as the Pi.
p
  | Appropriately, one of the first projects to be running (unmodified) on the Raspberry Pi was JBossAS7.
